    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hand work in textiles, wire, or other delicate materials that is decorative or ornamental, as opposed to strictly plain or functional. Fancy work includes needlework, crochet, knitting, hairwork, works using folded or woven paper as a medium (rather than or in addition to having paper as the support), metal wire, etc.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000015831/Niles, Fancy Work Recreations (1885)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De handwerken in textiel of andere fijne materialen die vooral decoratief zijn en niet zuiver praktisch en functioneel. De fraaie handwerken zijn borduren, haken, knopen, breien, haarwerk, werken met gevouwen of geweven papier, metaalvlechtwerk, etc.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>紡織品、金屬線或其他精緻材質所製作的手工品，具有點綴或裝飾性，與樸素無裝飾或純粹功能性作品有所不同。該類作品涵蓋針線縫製品、鉤針編織品、針織品、頭髮工藝品、折紙或織紙作品（以紙為底材之作品不在此內）、以及金屬線製品等。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
